    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear you, but resting just feels like more delay. if the music is gone, if the color is gone... what's actually left? it feels like there's no \"phase\" to pass through, just a void that's permanent. it's like reading a book where the last hundred pages are just blank. why would anyone want to keep turning the pages when there's nothing left to read?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
